Defendant Jonathan Earl Coleman-Wilks in court with attorney Daryl A. Kastenson.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy Court Clerk:  ss

Defendant sworn.
  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Plea questionnaire received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may not possess any firearms. No voting until civil rights are restored.

  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  


The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  3 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 121 days. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 and 1/2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 1 1/2 YEARS.
The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not the Substance Abuse Program.  The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 36 MONTHS with the following conditions.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No illegal drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers/houses);
*Cooperate with all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
* No contact with victim Travis L.;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school with part time employment;
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Pay all supervision fees;
-Complete a Cognitive Thinking/Behavior Program
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;
The Court ordered restitution to be determined on the next court date
Defendant is informed he/she may not possess and/or own any firearms.

Uoon successfull completition of probation the defendant may apply for expungement
Defendant is informed he/she may not vote in any election until his/her civil rights have been reinstated.  Appeal rights given. 
Filed;
